y=a\cos^3t\implies \cos^2t=\left(\frac{y}{a}\right)^{2/3}
x=a\sin^3t\implies \sin^2t=\left(\frac{x}{a}\right)^{2/3}
\cos^2t+\sin^2t=1
\implies \left(\frac{y}{a}\right)^{2/3}+\left(\frac{x}{a}\right)^{2/3}=1
\implies x^{2/3}+y^{2/3}=a^{2/3}
\implies y=(a^{2/3}-x^{2/3})^{3/2}
<y>=\frac{1}{a}\int_0^a(a^{2/3}-x^{2/3})^{3/2}dx
x=a\sin^3t
